Text: And to whomever ultimately wins between Regan and Jesse when the final votes are tallied, I wish you the best of luck going forward into the general election.

I also want to thank Regan, Jesse, and Terry for running a clean and respectful primary campaign.  It was an outlier to the other races, and I know many voters appreciated that.  It was a pleasure getting to know all of you during this process.

This support, along with your private messages of encouragement, really kept me going throughout this campaign and demonstrated that there is a desire for more civility and respect in our politics.  Thank you all!

This is all thanks to your help and support over the past few months: people who gathered signatures, put up signs, made donations, went door to door, hosted events, and did so many other things to spread our unifying message.

Our share of the vote was right about what I expected going into yesterday,  and given the outcomes in other races in Illinois, the fact that we met those expectations means we actually did BETTER than we should have!
When we started this campaign, we knew it was going to be an uphill climb since I would be running on a bipartisan message that is much different from a typical primary campaign.
Just got home from an all nighter of putting up signs at polling places across the district... Now it's your turn, please get out and vote. Polls are open until 7PM!

A huge thank you to the unsung heroes of our democracy: the poll workers.  Tomorrow is going to be a long day, and you don't get nearly enough gratitude. But your dedication to the electoral process is a true act of patriotism!
Just finished an interview with WCIA 3 News  in front of the state capitol. Check out the evening news tonight to hear our closing message ahead of tomorrow's primary! https://t.co/5Jk3vbu9GW
